 :tx/rationale "Create task: ACP-TEST-E2E: E2E test script scripts/e2e_acp.sh — validates ACP across the full CLI surface (INV-BUDGET-007, INV-BUDGET-008, INV-BUDGET-009). BACKGROUND: End-to-end validation that ACP works correctly across all converted commands at all k* levels. Each test runs braid commands with explicit --budget and --context-used flags to simulate different k* regimes, then validates the output structure. TESTS with [PASS]/[FAIL] and detailed logging: (1) braid status at budget=10 -> output starts with 'braid go' or 'braid harvest' (action present). (2) braid status at budget=300 -> output includes F(S), boundaries, tasks, action. (3) braid status at budget=10 output is SUBSET of budget=300 output (monotonic fill). (4) braid task ready at budget=50 -> shows top task as action, max 3 tasks in context. (5) braid task ready at budget=300 -> shows top-10+ tasks. (6) braid next at budget=10 -> shows action only (matches braid next at any budget). (7) NO output at any budget level contains '[...truncated' marker (the ACP guarantee). (8) braid status --context-used 0.8 (low k*) -> output is shorter than --context-used 0.0. (9) MCP braid_status response includes action field in JSON. (10) braid seed --task 'test' at budget=500 -> includes action + orientation + constraints. (11) All actions are executable braid commands (syntax check). (12) Timing: projection at each level completes in < 100ms. FILE: scripts/e2e_acp.sh"
